				<text>4.5.4.10 Exercise 10 Sum of currents</text>
		</name>
    <questiontext format="moodle_auto_format">
				<text><![CDATA[<p class="HELM_exercise">Exercise</p>
<p>Express the sum of&nbsp; two a.c. currents</p>
\[ i_1={@na5a*sin(omega*t+na5s1)@} \quad \text{and} \quad
i_2={@na5b*cos(omega*t + na5s2)@},\]
<p> in the form \(\displaystyle{A\cos\left(\omega t +&nbsp;\alpha\right)} \).</p>
<p>\( i_1+i_2= \) [[input:ans1]] [[validation:ans1]] [[feedback:prt1]]</p>
<p>Please write "pi" for the value \( \pi\) and "omega" for the parameter \( \omega\).</p>]]></text>
		</questiontext>
    <generalfeedback format="moodle_auto_format">
				<text><![CDATA[<p>We are given the two a.c. currents</p>
\[ i_1={@na5a*sin(omega*t+na5s1)@} \quad \text{and} \quad i_2={@na5b*cos(omega*t + na5s2)@}.\]
<p>Since \( \sin x=\cos\left(x-\dfrac{\pi}{2}\right)\) we have:</p>
<p>\( \sin\left(\omega t+{@na5s1@}\right)=\cos\left(\omega t+{@na5s1@}-\dfrac{\pi}{2}\right)= \cos \left(\omega t {@na5s2@}\right). \)</p>
<p>Therefore \( i_1+i_2={@na5a*cos(omega*t+na5s1-%pi/2)@} + {@na5b*cos(omega*t + na5s2)@}={@ta5f@}\)</p>]]></text>
		</generalfeedback>
